<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Croak" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Croak,</orth> vb. to caw, to cry as a raven: <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 191</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.264" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 264</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 33</bibl>. Transitively: <cit><quote>the raven himself is hoarse that --s the fatal entrance of Duncan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 40</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>